      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 1520: The re-invite path updates `conv-\u003einfo.members`, `conv-\u003einfo.mode`, and `conv-\u003ereinvitePending` without persisting the refreshed non-tombstone metadata. If the daemon restarts before the clone completes, the kept request allows retry, but the in-memory refresh is lost and the retry may run from stale tombstone metadata until the repository clone completes. Persist the request-derived metadata while preserving `removed`/`erased`, or explicitly refresh it again from the stored request before each retry path that depends on it.\n\n```suggestion\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.clear();\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.emplace(username_);\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.emplace(request.from);\n        conv-\u003einfo.mode \u003d request.mode();\n        conv-\u003ereinvitePending \u003d true;\n        addConvInfo(conv-\u003einfo);\n```",
