      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 2130: `deferRequestRemoval` is computed before `cloneConversationFrom()` marks `reinvitePending`, leaving a race where another local removal can clear `reinvitePending` and then `cloneConversationFrom()` sets it back to true. That would allow the older re-invitation to win over a newer removal, contradicting the comment on `reinvitePending`. Move the decision and marker update into one critical section, or make `cloneConversationFrom()` only set `reinvitePending` when the tombstone state has not changed since acceptance began.",
